header.gameNote: CAA MEN'S CHAMPIONSHIP - QUARTERFINAL AT RICHMOND VA

article.headline: Drexel 59, N.C.-Wilmington 47
article.story: RICHMOND, Va. -- Chris Fouch had 14 points to pace four double-figure scorers, leading Drexel over UNC Wilmington 59-47 on Saturday in the quarterfinal round of the Colonial Athletic Association tournament. The top-seeded Dragons, who had a bye in the first round, advanced to the semifinals on Sunday. Samme Givens and Frantz Massenat added 11 points apiece and Damion Lee poured in 10 for Drexel (26-5), which extended its winning streak to 18 straight games. The Dragons have won 24 of their last 25 overall. The game was tight for most of the first half, until Fouch had a jumper and a layup that helped fuel an 8-2 Drexel run that put the Dragons up for good. They led by five points at the break and outscored the ninth-seeded Seahawks 32-25 in the second half to seal it. Donte Morales had 13 points to lead UNC Wilmington (10-21).
